const throttledFoo = _.throttle( () => { console.log( sync ) }, 300, { leading: false } );

setInterval( () => {
	sync = true;
	throttledFoo();
	sync = false;
}, 500 );
```

My proposal is to change the way how `throttle` (and `debounce`) works to ensure they are always asynchronous.

**Motivation:**
Lot of times we need to pass a function that does this:
